{
  "video_id": "CtvIX4s1bTU",
  "title": "How humans could evolve to survive in space | Lisa Nip",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13800.0,
      "end_time": 17360.0,
      "text": "So there are lands few and far between on Earth itself"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17360.0,
      "end_time": 21440.0,
      "text": "that are hospitable to humans by any measure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 21440.0,
      "end_time": 23800.0,
      "text": "but survive we have."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 23800.0,
      "end_time": 28079.0,
      "text": "Our primitive ancestors, when they found their homes and livelihood endangered,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 28079.0,
      "end_time": 31240.0,
      "text": "they dared to make their way into unfamiliar territories"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 31240.0,
      "end_time": 33760.0,
      "text": "in search of better opportunities."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 33760.0,
      "end_time": 36000.0,
      "text": "And as the descendants of these explorers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 36000.0,
      "end_time": 40040.0,
      "text": "we have their nomadic blood coursing through our own veins."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 40040.0,
      "end_time": 41520.0,
      "text": "But at the same time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 41520.0,
      "end_time": 43640.0,
      "text": "distracted by our bread and circuses"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 43640.0,
      "end_time": 47840.0,
      "text": "and embroiled in the wars that we have waged on each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 47840.0,
      "end_time": 52320.0,
      "text": "it seems that we have forgotten this desire to explore."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 52320.0,
      "end_time": 56960.0,
      "text": "We, as a species, we&#39;re evolved uniquely"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 56960.0,
      "end_time": 61680.0,
      "text": "for Earth, on Earth, and by Earth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 61680.0,
      "end_time": 64840.0,
      "text": "and so content are we with our living conditions"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 64840.0,
      "end_time": 68280.0,
      "text": "that we have grown complacent and just too busy"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 68280.0,
      "end_time": 70760.0,
      "text": "to notice that its resources are finite,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 70760.0,
      "end_time": 74400.0,
      "text": "and that our Sun&#39;s life is also finite."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 74400.0,
      "end_time": 77200.0,
      "text": "While Mars and all the movies made in its name"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 77200.0,
      "end_time": 80240.0,
      "text": "have reinvigorated the ethos for space travel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 80240.0,
      "end_time": 85640.0,
      "text": "few of us seem to truly realize that our species&#39; fragile constitution"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 85640.0,
      "end_time": 90160.0,
      "text": "is woefully unprepared for long duration journeys into space."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 90160.0,
      "end_time": 92440.0,
      "text": "Let us take a trek to your local national forest"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 92440.0,
      "end_time": 94280.0,
      "text": "for a quick reality check."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 94280.0,
      "end_time": 96000.0,
      "text": "So just a quick show of hands here:"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 96000.0,
      "end_time": 99600.0,
      "text": "how many of you think you would be able to survive in this lush wilderness"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 99600.0,
      "end_time": 102000.0,
      "text": "for a few days?"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 102000.0,
      "end_time": 103320.0,
      "text": "Well, that&#39;s a lot of you."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 103320.0,
      "end_time": 106000.0,
      "text": "How about a few weeks?"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 106000.0,
      "end_time": 107280.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a decent amount."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 107280.0,
      "end_time": 109600.0,
      "text": "How about a few months?"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 109600.0,
      "end_time": 111120.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s pretty good too."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 111120.0,
      "end_time": 113800.0,
      "text": "Now, let us imagine that this local national forest"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 113800.0,
      "end_time": 117360.0,
      "text": "experiences an eternal winter."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 117360.0,
      "end_time": 122280.0,
      "text": "Same questions: how many of you think you would be able to survive for a few days?"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 122280.0,
      "end_time": 123720.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s quite a lot."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 123720.0,
      "end_time": 126400.0,
      "text": "How about a few weeks?"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 126400.0,
      "end_time": 131120.0,
      "text": "So for a fun twist, let us imagine that the only source of water available"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 131120.0,
      "end_time": 135080.0,
      "text": "is trapped as frozen blocks miles below the surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 135080.0,
      "end_time": 139200.0,
      "text": "Soil nutrients are so minimal that no vegetation can be found,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 139200.0,
      "end_time": 145240.0,
      "text": "and of course hardly any atmosphere exists to speak of."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 145240.0,
      "end_time": 149400.0,
      "text": "Such examples are only a few of the many challenges we would face"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 149400.0,
      "end_time": 152000.0,
      "text": "on a planet like Mars."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 152000.0,
      "end_time": 157200.0,
      "text": "So how do we steel ourselves for voyages whose destinations are so far removed"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 157200.0,
      "end_time": 159520.0,
      "text": "from a tropical vacation?"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 159520.0,
      "end_time": 162880.0,
      "text": "Will we continuously ship supplies from Planet Earth?"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 162880.0,
      "end_time": 166360.0,
      "text": "Build space elevators, or impossible miles of transport belts"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 166360.0,
      "end_time": 170160.0,
      "text": "that tether your planet of choice to our home planet?"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 170160.0,
      "end_time": 177080.0,
      "text": "And how do we grow things like food that grew up on Earth like us?"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 177080.0,
      "end_time": 179560.0,
      "text": "But I&#39;m getting ahead of myself."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 179560.0,
      "end_time": 183720.0,
      "text": "In our species&#39; journey to find a new home under a new sun,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 183720.0,
      "end_time": 187600.0,
      "text": "we are more likely than not going to be spending much time"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 187600.0,
      "end_time": 189840.0,
      "text": "in the journey itself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 189840.0,
      "end_time": 191480.0,
      "text": "in space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 191480.0,
      "end_time": 195120.0,
      "text": "on a ship, a hermetic flying can,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 195120.0,
      "end_time": 197480.0,
      "text": "possibly for many generations."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 197480.0,
      "end_time": 200920.0,
      "text": "The longest continuous amount of time that any human has spent in space"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 200920.0,
      "end_time": 204600.0,
      "text": "is in the vicinity of 12 to 14 months."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 204600.0,
      "end_time": 206960.0,
      "text": "From astronauts&#39; experiences in space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 206960.0,
      "end_time": 210760.0,
      "text": "we know that spending time in a microgravity environment"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 210760.0,
      "end_time": 215360.0,
      "text": "means bone loss, muscle atrophy, cardiovascular problems,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 215360.0,
      "end_time": 216960.0,
      "text": "among many other complications"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 216960.0,
      "end_time": 221200.0,
      "text": "that range for the physiological to the psychological."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 221200.0,
      "end_time": 222640.0,
      "text": "And what about macrogravity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 222640.0,
      "end_time": 225160.0,
      "text": "or any other variation in gravitational pull"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 225160.0,
      "end_time": 228560.0,
      "text": "of the planet that we find ourselves on?"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 228560.0,
      "end_time": 232120.0,
      "text": "In short, our cosmic voyages will be fraught with dangers"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 232120.0,
      "end_time": 234960.0,
      "text": "both known and unknown."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 234960.0,
      "end_time": 239000.0,
      "text": "So far we&#39;ve been looking to this new piece of mechanical technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 239000.0,
      "end_time": 241280.0,
      "text": "or that great next generation robot"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 241280.0,
      "end_time": 245600.0,
      "text": "as part of a lineup to ensure our species safe passage in space."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 245600.0,
      "end_time": 248560.0,
      "text": "Wonderful as they are, I believe the time has come"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 248560.0,
      "end_time": 252840.0,
      "text": "for us to complement these bulky electronic giants"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 252840.0,
      "end_time": 256320.0,
      "text": "with what nature has already invented:"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 256320.0,
      "end_time": 257720.0,
      "text": "the microbe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 257720.00000000003,
      "end_time": 262960.0,
      "text": "a single-celled organism that is itself a self-generating, self-replenishing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 262960.0,
      "end_time": 264760.0,
      "text": "living machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 264760.0,
      "end_time": 267200.0,
      "text": "It requires fairly little to maintain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 267200.0,
      "end_time": 269120.0,
      "text": "offers much flexibility in design"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 269120.0,
      "end_time": 273399.0,
      "text": "and only asks to be carried in a single plastic tube."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 273399.0,
      "end_time": 277280.0,
      "text": "The field of study that has enabled us to utilize the capabilities of the microbe"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 277280.0,
      "end_time": 279520.0,
      "text": "is known as synthetic biology."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 279520.0,
      "end_time": 283560.0,
      "text": "It comes from molecular biology, which has given us antibiotics, vaccines"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 283560.0,
      "end_time": 286880.0,
      "text": "and better ways to observe the physiological nuances"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 286880.0,
      "end_time": 288520.0,
      "text": "of the human body."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 288520.0,
      "end_time": 290520.0,
      "text": "Using the tools of synthetic biology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 290520.0,
      "end_time": 293480.0,
      "text": "we can now edit the genes of nearly any organism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 293480.0,
      "end_time": 295440.0,
      "text": "microscopic or not,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 295440.0,
      "end_time": 298760.0,
      "text": "with incredible speed and fidelity."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 298760.0,
      "end_time": 301680.0,
      "text": "Given the limitations of our man-made machines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 301680.0,
      "end_time": 305680.0,
      "text": "synthetic biology will be a means for us to engineer not only our food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 305680.0,
      "end_time": 308440.0,
      "text": "our fuel and our environment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 308440.0,
      "end_time": 310760.0,
      "text": "but also ourselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 310760.0,
      "end_time": 313400.0,
      "text": "to compensate for our physical inadequacies"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 313400.0,
      "end_time": 317000.0,
      "text": "and to ensure our survival in space."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 317000.0,
      "end_time": 318240.0,
      "text": "To give you an example"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 318240.0,
      "end_time": 321080.0,
      "text": "of how we can use synthetic biology for space exploration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 321080.0,
      "end_time": 324160.0,
      "text": "let us return to the Mars environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 324160.0,
      "end_time": 328920.0,
      "text": "The Martian soil composition is similar to that of Hawaiian volcanic ash,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 328920.0,
      "end_time": 331400.0,
      "text": "with trace amounts of organic material."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 331400.0,
      "end_time": 333680.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s say, hypothetically,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 333680.0,
      "end_time": 336440.0,
      "text": "what if martian soil could actually support plant growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 336440.0,
      "end_time": 339360.0,
      "text": "without using Earth-derived nutrients?"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 339360.0,
      "end_time": 341480.0,
      "text": "The first question we should probably ask is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 341480.0,
      "end_time": 343880.0,
      "text": "how would we make our plants cold-tolerant?"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 343880.0,
      "end_time": 346000.0,
      "text": "Because, on average, the temperature on Mars"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 346000.0,
      "end_time": 350000.0,
      "text": "is a very uninviting negative 60 degrees centigrade."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 350000.0,
      "end_time": 351800.0,
      "text": "The next question we should ask is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 351800.0,
      "end_time": 354280.0,
      "text": "how do we make our plants drought-tolerant?"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 354280.0,
      "end_time": 357120.0,
      "text": "Considering that most of the water that forms as frost"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 357120.0,
      "end_time": 361120.0,
      "text": "evaporates more quickly than I can say the word &quot;evaporate.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 361120.0,
      "end_time": 364480.0,
      "text": "Well, it turns out we&#39;ve already done things like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 364480.0,
      "end_time": 367800.0,
      "text": "By borrowing genes for anti-freeze protein from fish"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 367800.0,
      "end_time": 371000.0,
      "text": "and genes for drought tolerance from other plants like rice"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 371000.0,
      "end_time": 373720.0,
      "text": "and then stitching them into the plants that need them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 373720.0,
      "end_time": 377480.0,
      "text": "we now have plants that can tolerate most droughts and freezes."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 377480.0,
      "end_time": 380120.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re known on Earth as GMOs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 380120.0,
      "end_time": 382680.0,
      "text": "or genetically modified organisms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 382680.0,
      "end_time": 388160.0,
      "text": "and we rely on them to feed all the mouths of human civilization."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 388160.0,
      "end_time": 391600.0,
      "text": "Nature does stuff like this already,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 391600.0,
      "end_time": 393160.0,
      "text": "without our help."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 393160.0,
      "end_time": 397480.0,
      "text": "We have simply found more precise ways to do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 397480.0,
      "end_time": 402120.0,
      "text": "So why would we want to change the genetic makeup of plants for space?"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 402120.0,
      "end_time": 405720.0,
      "text": "Well, to not do so would mean needing to engineer"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 405720.0,
      "end_time": 409160.0,
      "text": "endless acres of land on an entirely new planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 409160.0,
      "end_time": 412680.0,
      "text": "by releasing trillions of gallons of atmospheric gasses"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 412680.0,
      "end_time": 416480.0,
      "text": "and then constructing a giant glass dome to contain it all."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 416480.0,
      "end_time": 418560.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s an unrealistic engineering enterprise"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 418560.0,
      "end_time": 423240.0,
      "text": "that quickly becomes a high-cost cargo transport mission."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 423240.0,
      "end_time": 424720.0,
      "text": "One of the best ways to ensure"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 424720.0,
      "end_time": 427840.0,
      "text": "that we will have the food supplies and the air that we need"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 427840.0,
      "end_time": 430960.0,
      "text": "is to bring with us organisms that have been engineered"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 430960.0,
      "end_time": 434760.0,
      "text": "to adapt to new and harsh environments."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 434760.0,
      "end_time": 438760.0,
      "text": "In essence, using engineered organisms to help us terraform a planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 438760.0,
      "end_time": 442400.0,
      "text": "both in the short and long term."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 442400.0,
      "end_time": 447920.0,
      "text": "These organisms can then also be engineered to make medicine or fuel."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 447920.0,
      "end_time": 451680.0,
      "text": "So we can use synthetic biology to bring highly engineered plants with us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 451680.0,
      "end_time": 453880.0,
      "text": "but what else can we do?"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 453880.0,
      "end_time": 456760.0,
      "text": "Well, I mentioned earlier that we, as a species,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 456760.0,
      "end_time": 459800.0,
      "text": "were evolved uniquely for planet Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 459800.0,
      "end_time": 462440.0,
      "text": "That fact has not changed much in the last five minutes"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 462440.0,
      "end_time": 465480.0,
      "text": "that you were sitting here and I was standing there."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 465480.0,
      "end_time": 469200.0,
      "text": "And so, if we were to dump any of us on Mars right this minute,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 469200.0,
      "end_time": 472720.0,
      "text": "even given ample food, water, air"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 472720.0,
      "end_time": 473960.0,
      "text": "and a suit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 473960.0,
      "end_time": 477360.0,
      "text": "we are likely to experience very unpleasant health problems"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 477360.0,
      "end_time": 480680.0,
      "text": "from the amount of ionizing radiation that bombards the surface"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 480680.0,
      "end_time": 485280.0,
      "text": "of planets like Mars that have little or nonexistent atmosphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 485280.0,
      "end_time": 487320.0,
      "text": "Unless we plan to stay holed up underground"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 487320.0,
      "end_time": 490480.0,
      "text": "for the duration of our stay on every new planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 490480.0,
      "end_time": 493080.0,
      "text": "we must find better ways of protecting ourselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 493080.0,
      "end_time": 495760.0,
      "text": "without needing to resort to wearing a suit of armor"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 495760.0,
      "end_time": 498240.0,
      "text": "that weighs something equal to your own body weight,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 498240.0,
      "end_time": 502240.0,
      "text": "or needing to hide behind a wall of lead."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 502240.0,
      "end_time": 506200.0,
      "text": "So let us appeal to nature for inspiration."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 506200.0,
      "end_time": 508320.0,
      "text": "Among the plethora of life here on Earth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 508320.0,
      "end_time": 511200.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s a subset of organisms known as extremophiles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 511200.0,
      "end_time": 513200.0,
      "text": "or lovers of extreme living conditions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 513200.00000000006,
      "end_time": 515680.00000000006,
      "text": "if you&#39;ll remember from high school biology."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 515679.99999999994,
      "end_time": 521039.99999999994,
      "text": "And among these organisms is a bacterium by the name of Deinococcus radiodurans."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 521039.99999999994,
      "end_time": 526440.0,
      "text": "It is known to be able to withstand cold, dehydration, vacuum, acid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 526440.0,
      "end_time": 529440.0,
      "text": "and, most notably, radiation."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 529440.0,
      "end_time": 532159.0,
      "text": "While its radiation tolerance mechanisms are known,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 532159.0,
      "end_time": 535520.0,
      "text": "we have yet to adapt the relevant genes to mammals."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 535520.0,
      "end_time": 538160.0,
      "text": "To do so is not particularly easy."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 538160.0,
      "end_time": 541000.0,
      "text": "There are many facets that go into its radiation tolerance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 541000.0,
      "end_time": 543960.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s not as simple as transferring one gene."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 543960.0,
      "end_time": 547240.0,
      "text": "But given a little bit of human ingenuity"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 547240.0,
      "end_time": 548520.0,
      "text": "and a little bit of time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 548520.0,
      "end_time": 552000.0,
      "text": "I think to do so is not very hard either."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 552000.0,
      "end_time": 558400.0,
      "text": "Even if we borrow just a fraction of its ability to tolerate radiation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 558400.0,
      "end_time": 561440.0,
      "text": "it would be infinitely better than what we already have,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 561440.0,
      "end_time": 564560.0,
      "text": "which is just the melanin in our skin."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 564560.0,
      "end_time": 566600.0,
      "text": "Using the tools of synthetic biology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 566600.0,
      "end_time": 569640.0,
      "text": "we can harness Deinococcus radiodurans&#39; ability"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 569640.0,
      "end_time": 575760.0,
      "text": "to thrive under otherwise very lethal doses of radiation."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 575760.0,
      "end_time": 577920.0,
      "text": "As difficult as it is to see,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 577920.0,
      "end_time": 581200.0,
      "text": "homo sapiens, that is humans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 581200.0,
      "end_time": 583520.0,
      "text": "evolves every day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 583520.0,
      "end_time": 586360.0,
      "text": "and still continues to evolve."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 586360.0,
      "end_time": 588160.0,
      "text": "Thousands of years of human evolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 588160.0,
      "end_time": 591160.0,
      "text": "has not only given us humans like Tibetans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 591160.0,
      "end_time": 593760.0,
      "text": "who can thrive in low-oxygen conditions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 593760.0,
      "end_time": 598720.0,
      "text": "but also Argentinians, who can ingest and metabolize arsenic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 598720.0,
      "end_time": 602360.0,
      "text": "the chemical element that can kill the average human being."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 602360.0,
      "end_time": 606080.0,
      "text": "Every day, the human body evolves by accidental mutations"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 606080.0,
      "end_time": 608960.0,
      "text": "that equally accidentally allow certain humans"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 608960.0,
      "end_time": 612160.0,
      "text": "to persevere in dismal situations."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 612160.0,
      "end_time": 615480.0,
      "text": "But, and this is a big but,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 615480.0,
      "end_time": 619680.0,
      "text": "such evolution requires two things that we may not always have,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 619680.0,
      "end_time": 622120.0,
      "text": "or be able to afford,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 622120.0,
      "end_time": 625560.0,
      "text": "and they are death and time."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 625560.0,
      "end_time": 628600.0,
      "text": "In our species&#39; struggle to find our place in the universe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 628600.0,
      "end_time": 631080.0,
      "text": "we may not always have the time necessary"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 631080.0,
      "end_time": 633640.0,
      "text": "for the natural evolution of extra functions"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 633640.0,
      "end_time": 636360.0,
      "text": "for survival on non-Earth planets."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 636360.0,
      "end_time": 640880.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re living in what E.O. Wilson has termed the age of gene circumvention,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 640880.0,
      "end_time": 646280.0,
      "text": "during which we remedy our genetic defects like cystic fibrosis or muscular dystrophy"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 646280.0,
      "end_time": 649960.0,
      "text": "with temporary external supplements."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 649960.0,
      "end_time": 651520.0,
      "text": "But with every passing day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 651520.0,
      "end_time": 654720.0,
      "text": "we approach the age of volitional evolution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 654720.0,
      "end_time": 656720.0,
      "text": "a time during which we as a species"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 656720.0,
      "end_time": 662720.0,
      "text": "will have the capacity to decide for ourselves our own genetic destiny."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 662720.0,
      "end_time": 665080.0,
      "text": "Augmenting the human body with new abilities"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 665080.0,
      "end_time": 667920.0,
      "text": "is no longer a question of how,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 667920.0,
      "end_time": 670240.0,
      "text": "but of when."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 670240.0,
      "end_time": 671520.0,
      "text": "Using synthetic biology"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 671520.0,
      "end_time": 674640.0,
      "text": "to change the genetic makeup of any living organisms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 674640.0,
      "end_time": 675880.0,
      "text": "especially our own,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 675880.0,
      "end_time": 679280.0,
      "text": "is not without its moral and ethical quandaries."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 679280.0,
      "end_time": 682960.0,
      "text": "Will engineering ourselves make us less human?"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 682960.0,
      "end_time": 685240.0,
      "text": "But then again, what is humanity"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 685240.0,
      "end_time": 689200.0,
      "text": "but star stuff that happens to be conscious?"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 689200.0,
      "end_time": 692640.0,
      "text": "Where should human genius direct itself?"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 692640.0,
      "end_time": 697800.0,
      "text": "Surely it is a bit of a waste to sit back and marvel at it."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 697800.0,
      "end_time": 699160.0,
      "text": "How do we use our knowledge"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 699160.0,
      "end_time": 702440.0,
      "text": "to protect ourselves from the external dangers"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 702440.0,
      "end_time": 706400.0,
      "text": "and then protect ourselves from ourselves?"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 706400.0,
      "end_time": 707840.0,
      "text": "I pose these questions"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 707840.0,
      "end_time": 710040.0,
      "text": "not to engender the fear of science"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 710040.0,
      "end_time": 712440.0,
      "text": "but to bring to light the many possibilities"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 712440.0,
      "end_time": 716760.0,
      "text": "that science has afforded and continues to afford us."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 716760.0,
      "end_time": 720760.0,
      "text": "We must coalesce as humans to discuss and embrace the solutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 720760.0,
      "end_time": 722640.0,
      "text": "not only with caution"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 722640.0,
      "end_time": 726200.0,
      "text": "but also with courage."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 726200.0,
      "end_time": 730440.0,
      "text": "Mars is a destination,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 730440.0,
      "end_time": 733000.0,
      "text": "but it will not be our last."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 733000.0,
      "end_time": 735880.0,
      "text": "Our true final frontier is the line we must cross"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 735880.0,
      "end_time": 741880.0,
      "text": "in deciding what we can and should make of our species&#39; improbable intelligence."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 741880.0,
      "end_time": 747120.0,
      "text": "Space is cold, brutal and unforgiving."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 747120.0,
      "end_time": 749560.0,
      "text": "Our path to the stars will be rife with trials"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 749560.0,
      "end_time": 752560.0,
      "text": "that will bring us to question not only who we are"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 752560.0,
      "end_time": 755160.0,
      "text": "but where we will be going."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 755160.0,
      "end_time": 758760.0,
      "text": "The answers will lie in our choice to use or abandon the technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 758760.0,
      "end_time": 760880.0,
      "text": "that we have gleaned from life itself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 760880.0,
      "end_time": 764760.0,
      "text": "and it will define us for the remainder of our term in this universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 764760.0,
      "end_time": 766000.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 766000.0,
      "end_time": 776000.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}